Result: false  
Justification:  
The condition C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. Here, the claim is "Isaac is confident." The P-type arguments are both against the claim (they argue that Isaac does not gain confidence and therefore cannot be confident). However, the S-type arguments are also against the claim (they support the conclusion that Isaac is self-doubting, not confident). This means there is no P-type argument whose justification contains a semantic subset from an S-type argument that supports the claim. Since all provided arguments oppose the claim, C11 is not satisfied.